oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Map, 2nd, 7th, and 10th Regts.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Map indicating the regions of Middle Tennessee in which the Second, Seventh, and Tenth Regiments of the Tennessee State Guard operated. Also shows county boundaries, main highways, and railroads.

With the reorganization of the Tennessee State Guard in May of 1942, these regiments combined to comprise the Second Brigade, commanded by Brig. Gen. Jacob McGavock Dickinson and headquartered in Nashville.
